question_title: Could you pls specify some budgeting basics? [SEP] question_content:  [SEP] best_answer: Budgeting involves planning your and/or your family's revenue and expenditure. Basic things you need to do related to this are:

* Monitor expenditure and revenue;

* Review your budget periodically as a result of this new information or to set new goals;

* Have a 60-40 rule with 60% in fixed bills and rent and 40% on discretionary expenditure and 10% on irregular expenditure, savings goals, retirement and fun;

* Try to have your rent or mortgage at now more than 25% of the budget;

* As far as possible, Keep It Simple Stupid.
